During my six months as a data intern with The Post's investigative team, I contributed analysis and graphics to long and short-term projects. We are currently investigating aggressive campaign tactics that may have crossed legal boundaries in a recent election.

I wrote code that processed thousands of bills to trace model legislation and influence to its source, used government and open-source APIs to automate data-gathering and wrote about sparsely reported lobbyist expenditures.
I covered community, crime and cold cases for The Arizona Republic, KPNX 12 News and azcentral.com, in addition to collecting and analyzing crime data for stories.
